The paper discusses an approach to goal recognition using recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach is evaluated in image-based domains, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The goal recognition task is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY) as it can be used to improve the autonomy and decision-making capabilities of robots and autonomous systems.
